the s7g reactor was a prototype naval reactor designed for the united states navy to provide electricity generation and propulsion on warships. the s7g designation stands for: 
*  s = submarine platform 
*  7 = seventh reactor designed by the contractor 
*  g = general electric was the contracted designer this prototype design was a land-based nuclear reactor that did not use control rods. it was tested in the late 1970s and early 1980s at the modifications and additions to a reactor facility (marf) plant located at the knolls atomic power laboratory's kesselring site in ballston spa, new york. it consisted of an experimental reactor core installed in a modified s5w reactor plant.